								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p1",
									"fallback": "We were visiting the imprisoned child, as we did every evening to provide comfort and warmth, when we lowered our guard."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p2",
									"fallback": "In seconds, Odin fell. Only the hero of Svartalfheim remains."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p3",
									"fallback": "Before disappearing, I remember a discussion with Odin, he had told me that in Asgard too, the incarnations passed messages to each other."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p4",
									"fallback": "And that Helheim has never won a single war - our offensive power is too weak, and we had to rely on our Necromancer abilities."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p5",
									"fallback": "But it's unthinkable to do that knowing the truth about the beings of this world. As for Asgard, they have won several times."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p6",
									"fallback": "Victory brings the power of Ragnar√∂k - the ability to rewrite the rules of the world for the next game."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p7",
									"fallback": "If I win, I can save them and all the immortals."
								},
								{
									"translate": "item.yggdrasil.helheim.chronicles.ch7.p8",
									"fallback": "I must win, or else do it in my place!"
								}
